wdr:trigger-apple-macintosh a drift:TriggerEvent ;
    rdfs:label "Apple Macintosh launch and personal computing revolution"@en ;
    dct:description "Engelbart's team coined the device name in 1965; the launch of the Apple Macintosh in 1984 and the spread of GUI-based personal computers brought the computer 'mouse' metaphor into mainstream English vocabulary."@en,
        "The launch of the Apple Macintosh in 1984 and the subsequent spread of GUI-based personal computers brought the computer 'mouse' metaphor into mainstream German vocabulary."@en ;
    owl:sameAs wd:Q1137478 ;
    drift:eventDate "1984"^^xsd:gYear ;
    drift:triggerCategory drift:Technology .

wdr:trigger-aws-launch a drift:TriggerEvent ;
    rdfs:label "Amazon Web Services launch and popularisation of cloud computing (2006)"@en ;
    dct:description "Amazon's launch of AWS EC2 and S3 in 2006 and the global spread of 'cloud computing' anchored the metaphor; German adopted 'die Cloud / die Wolke' for networked storage and compute shortly afterwards."@en,
        "Amazon's launch of AWS EC2 and S3 in 2006, followed by Eric Schmidt's use of 'cloud computing' at the 2006 Search Engine Strategies conference, anchored the term in mainstream technology discourse."@en ;
    owl:sameAs wd:Q456157 ;
    drift:eventDate "2006"^^xsd:gYear ;
    drift:triggerCategory drift:Technology .

wdr:trigger-computer-virus a drift:TriggerEvent ;
    rdfs:label "naming of the computer virus and early PC infections"@en ;
    dct:description "Fred Cohen defined and named the 'computer virus' in 1983-1984 academic work; the Brain boot-sector virus (1986) and the spread of personal computers carried the term into mainstream English."@en,
        "Fred Cohen defined and named the 'computer virus' in 1983-1984; the Brain virus (1986) and the spread of personal computers carried the term into German as 'Computervirus'."@en ;
    owl:sameAs wd:Q14001 ;
    drift:eventDate "1984"^^xsd:gYear ;
    drift:triggerCategory drift:Technology .

wdr:trigger-ecology-movement a drift:TriggerEvent ;
    rdfs:label "the modern environmental movement and the rise of Green politics"@en ;
    dct:description "The environmental movement of the 1970s-80s (Earth Day 1970, Greenpeace 1971, and the founding of Green parties) attached an ecological-political meaning to 'green', making it shorthand for environmentally friendly."@en ;
    drift:eventDate "1972"^^xsd:gYear ;
    drift:triggerCategory drift:Political .

wdr:trigger-facebook-like a drift:TriggerEvent ;
    rdfs:label "Facebook Like button launch (2009)"@en ;
    dct:description "Facebook launched its 'Like' button (German 'Gefaellt mir') in 2009; the feature made the borrowed verb 'liken' the common German term for one-click social endorsement."@en,
        "Facebook launched its 'Like' button in February 2009; the feature spread across the web and social platforms, turning the everyday verb into a one-click social endorsement and a countable noun ('likes')."@en ;
    owl:sameAs wd:Q355 ;
    drift:eventDate "2009"^^xsd:gYear ;
    drift:triggerCategory drift:Technology .

wdr:trigger-ftp-mirroring a drift:TriggerEvent ;
    rdfs:label "rise of internet FTP mirror sites"@en ;
    dct:description "As anonymous-FTP archives and software distribution grew across the early internet, popular archives were duplicated onto 'mirror' servers to share load and improve access, fixing the computing sense in the early 1990s."@en,
        "As anonymous-FTP archives spread across the early internet, popular archives were duplicated onto 'mirror' servers; German 'spiegeln' took on the computing sense for server and disk mirroring in the 1990s."@en ;
    drift:eventDate "1991"^^xsd:gYear ;
    drift:triggerCategory drift:Technology .

