wdr:trigger-www-mosaic a drift:TriggerEvent ;
    rdfs:label "World Wide Web and Mosaic browser launch"@en ;
    dct:description "The public launch of the WWW and graphical browsers (Mosaic 1993, Netscape 1994) brought the internet to a mass audience; German adopted 'das Netz' for the internet and the web, mirroring the English 'web' metaphor."@en,
        "The public launch of the WWW and graphical browsers (Mosaic 1993, Netscape 1994) popularised 'surfing the internet'; Jean Armour Polly's 1992 article coined the phrase in English, which entered German as 'im Internet surfen'."@en,
        "The public launch of the WWW and graphical browsers (Mosaic 1993, Netscape 1994) popularised 'surfing the web'; Jean Armour Polly's 1992 article coined the phrase 'surfing the internet'."@en,
        "Tim Berners-Lee proposed the World Wide Web in 1989 and named it, drawing on the spider-web metaphor of interlinked documents; graphical browsers (Mosaic 1993, Netscape 1994) made 'the web' a household word."@en ;
    owl:sameAs wd:Q381047 ;
    drift:eventDate "1993"^^xsd:gYear ;
    drift:triggerCategory drift:Technology .

